textRun.content: We often hear partner feedback stating that partners don’t see any jobs on their job board. In December of 2025, we implemented event tracking to see the jobs shown on a partner’s job board each time an event is triggered (view page, refresh, etc).
The purpose of this document is to share out the findings from a deep dive into the number of job offers shown on a partner’s job board.
The job board is failing to present sufficient job offers
50% of partner-visits resulting in zero offers
97.4% of all offers shown being jobs the partner has already been offered
. This directly impacts partner satisfaction, as partners who see fewer jobs have much lower Partner NPS (-22) vs others (around 0).

Section 1: When partners land on/refresh the job board, they don’t see many job offers

These findings are based on data from 2,581 partners regardless of country/approval/limits/outsourcing group/etc who came to the job board and triggered an event (visits the job board, refreshes the job board, etc) during the timeline.
The number of jobs offered at the event level for all partners

At the event level for all partners, 50% of events result in zero offers being shown. The average is 4 job offers, although those 4 job offers include largely the same job offers they have seen before.
The number of jobs offered at the event level by partner outsourcing group

By outsourcing group, the average number of job offers shown are as follows: Default Group sees ~2 jobs per event, Expanded Premium Group sees ~2 jobs per event, Premium sees ~14 jobs per event, Expanded Ultra Premium sees ~12 jobs per event, Ultra Premium sees ~16 jobs per event, Expanded Elite sees ~5 jobs per event, and Elite sees ~4 jobs per event.
Looking at only domestic and approved partners (2,204 partners),
a similar (slightly better) pattern is found across
all partner outsourcing groups, except for premium partners (13.7 to 1.3), likely due to international partners having a lot of offers.
The number of jobs offered at the event level by partner outsourcing group among partners who are domestic and approved
Section 2: In addition to not seeing many job offers, partners often see the same offers over and over again

Section 3: Partners are more satisfied with Xometry when they see more job offers
Partner NPS score generally increases as partners see more jobs from -22 at the lowest job offer count bin (less than 4 job offers) to 13 at the highest job offer bin (more than 53 job offers).
Partner NPS score by number of new jobs offered bin
Avan Vora recently did an analysis that looks into job board visits and acceptance/margin. The analysis can be found

We plan to investigate partner job board habits and patterns of new offers/lack of new offers that may lead to job board visits decreasing. We are limited on this piece due to churn being based on 90 days with us only having ~40 days of data.

These findings are based on data from 2,581 partners regardless of country/approval/limits/outsourcing group/etc who came to the job board and triggered an event (visits the job board, refreshes the job board, etc) during the timeline.
Fraction of Partners Included based on Jobs Completed Bin

Image 1 indicates the number of jobs the partners included have taken to gain an understanding of who we are looking at, where it can be seen that ~72% of the partners included have accepted beyond six jobs in their entire duration with Xometry.
The fraction of partners included by outsourcing group
Image 2 shows that ~63% of the partners included are in Default or Expanded Premium outsourcing groups.
